This new species is characterized by small size (SVL of males 18.8–23.2, n = 26; SVL of females 20.1–27.5, n = 5); subovoid snout in dorsal view; 
canthus rostralis
marked; loreal region concave and oblique; vocal slits present in males; males with vocal sac not expanded; presence of glandular acini on the mental region (
Fig. 3
); absence of macroscopic glandular acini on the pectoral region; pectoral fold absent; absence of macroscopic glandular acini on the medial region of the forearm; presence of macroscopic glandular acini on the dorsal region of the Fingers II and III; nuptial pad with the glandular acini diffuse over the skin and not cohesive, not forming an elevated structure on the skin; interocular region with a w-shape blotch that exceeds the posterior margin of the eyes; skin on dorsum smooth; belly and gular region cream with irregular lines and scattered dots; absence of bright coloration on inguinal region and hidden portions of the thigh and shank; presence of inguinal gland (
Fig. 4
); the foot webbing reaches the second subarticular tubercles or at most a half of the penultimate phalanx of Toe V.

